Born on 21st July 1977 in Ankara, **Mehmet Turgut** is a third-generation photography artist, creative director, and designer. His destiny was written by his grandfather Mehmet Turgut who was also a photographer and his name father. His grandfather was one of the first photographers in Turkey. When he lost his father at age of 7, he had to work various jobs to take care of his family. His grandfather, who embarked on an adventure in photography after his art teacher sold his camera to him, who saw that he was talented in painting, started to earn his living from photography at the age of 9 during those difficult times of the first world war. At the same time, his grandmother Emine Lady was one of the first female photographers in Turkey. This art reached from grandfather and grandmother to uncle and father, and from there to Mehmet Turgut. For many years, he worked on theoretical photography, printing techniques, coloring, and photo editing. In more recent years, **Mehmet** worked on fictional photography and the art of photography.
&nbsp;
**Mehmet** has won several national and international awards for his work, including awards from the Photographic Society of America and Austria Super Circuit. He also has given many workshops and talks in various institutions such as TEDx Istanbul and the Massachusetts Institute of Technology. **Mehmet** created record covers of Patricia Kaas’ “Best Of” and Ozzy Osbourne’s “Let It Die”. He has worked with many international Rock artists such as Alice Cooper, Anthrax, Hail, Scorpions, Soulfly, Volbeat, Iced Earth and international brands such as Coca Cola, Redbull, Pepsi, Unilever, P&G, Nike, Ford, Jack Daniels and etc.. He is brand ambassador of National Geopraphic and Unicef.
&nbsp;
In 2009, **Mehmet** was given the “Photography Artist of the Year” award by the Turkish Art Institution. In 2014, he won the “Photographer of the Year” award the One Eye Land Awards. Mehmet has been the owner and the creative director of the “Karakalem” Magazine since 2008 and the “46” Magazine since 2010. He also published his first photographic book “30” in 2012. In 2014, **Mehmet** created the project “Ala Portreler” with names like Ara Guler and Aydin Boysan. He opened his first international exhibition at the Rome Expo Sabatini in Italy. He continues to produce visual consultancy and content for literary magazines such as Kafa, Ot, Tuhaf, and to work at universities as a lecturer...

