&nbsp;

Why do we feel so nostalgic about it even if we were not alive at that time? That's a question no one can really explain and will probably stay a mystery.

This is a project where I have tried not to tell the story from one lens, but focus on how individual audiences can imagine their own story just by looking at the pieces. I feel the way you lived your life will always reflect back on something whether it's art, a story, or your culture. How do we, as an audience build perception towards it? That's an interesting question... It is up to you as the consumer to choose your own story. 

