drops.creatorInfo:
**Kagan Okudan**, is an LA-based Motion Designer and Director. From an early age, he was heavily inspired by nature especially with the concept of biomimicry and how we as humans have adapted natural processes to our benefit. With time this attitude turned into a lifestyle for him. Through this approach, he was able to hone and develop his problem-solving skills, which became vital for his work when he was often presented with tight deadlines.
&nbsp;
It was during his studies in Vienna, he met his inspirations; Zaha Hadid and Greg Lynn and, it was at this moment he realized his life had changed forever. Initially, he would explore media forms such as photography, videography and then eventually found 3D design in the end. Afterward, he began studying visual communication design in Istanbul and focused more on motion design and direction.
&nbsp;
After spending some time in Istanbul he moved to LA, Kagan would then gain certifications in schools like the school of motion and Gnomon. Kagan has contributed and collaborated with artists such as Cardi B, J Balvin, and Kali Uchis and worked with brands such as Segway Robotics. He is also a proud member of the in-house directors of Underscorefilms as of late.

